## 12. Implementation Checklist

Use this checklist when building hybrid search for a new project:

### FTS Layer
- [ ] Set up SQLite FTS5 virtual table (`CREATE VIRTUAL TABLE ... USING fts5(...)`)
- [ ] Use `buildFtsQuery()` pattern: AND-join quoted tokens, Unicode-aware tokenizer (`[\p{L}\p{N}_]+`)
- [ ] Convert BM25 rank to normalized score: `1 / (1 + max(0, rank))`
- [ ] Handle FTS-only mode: search all model fingerprints when embedding provider is absent
- [ ] Truncate snippets safely (UTF-16 aware) before storing in results

### Vector Layer
- [ ] Prefer `sqlite-vec` extension for in-database cosine distance (`vec_distance_cosine`)
- [ ] Implement JS cosine similarity fallback for when the extension is unavailable
- [ ] Store query vector as `Float32Array` binary blob
- [ ] Convert distance to similarity: `score = 1 - cosineDistance`
- [ ] Pin results to current embedding model fingerprint (model name + endpoint)

### Merge Layer
- [ ] Union by chunk ID, not by path (multiple chunks per file)
- [ ] Default weights: vectorWeight = 0.7, textWeight = 0.3 (sum must equal 1.0)
- [ ] Prefer keyword snippet over vector snippet when same chunk appears in both pools
- [ ] Fetch `candidateMultiplier × maxResults` from each pool before merge (default: 4×)

### Temporal Decay
- [ ] Parse date from `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` path pattern (UTC, not local time)
- [ ] Detect evergreen files (MEMORY.md, non-dated memory/*.md) → skip decay
- [ ] Fall back to file mtime for non-memory sources
- [ ] Cache timestamp resolution per file to avoid redundant fs.stat calls
- [ ] Default halfLifeDays = 30; adjust for your data retention window

### MMR Re-ranking
- [ ] Normalize scores to [0, 1] using min-max before MMR computation
- [ ] Use Jaccard similarity on tokenized snippet text (not re-embedding)
- [ ] Pre-tokenize all candidates once before the iterative selection loop
- [ ] Default λ = 0.7; document how to tune toward diversity (↓λ) or relevance (↑λ)
- [ ] Provide a tiebreaker (original score) for equal MMR scores

### Query Expansion
- [ ] Apply stop word filtering for each language in your corpus
- [ ] Handle CJK: character n-grams (unigrams + bigrams for Chinese/Japanese)
- [ ] Handle Korean: strip trailing particles, emit both forms
- [ ] Drop vague time references as FTS tokens (yesterday, today, etc.)
- [ ] Format: `original OR keyword1 OR keyword2` for broader recall
- [ ] Provide an optional LLM expander with local extraction fallback

### Fallback & Reliability
- [ ] Implement `FallbackMemoryManager` pattern: primary → fallback on first failure
- [ ] Evict the primary from cache on failure so next session retries fresh
- [ ] Never throw from the fallback path — return empty results + log warning
- [ ] Degrade gracefully: QMD → SQLite hybrid → FTS-only → empty
- [ ] Default scope: deny memory recall in group/public channels

