## 13. Tuning Guide

### Finding the right vector/text weight split

Start with `0.7 / 0.3`. If you observe:
- **High recall for natural language but missing exact IDs/symbols** → increase textWeight toward 0.4–0.5
- **Good keyword recall but missing paraphrased content** → increase vectorWeight toward 0.8
- **FTS matching completely irrelevant documents** → tighten the FTS query (AND instead of OR), or lower candidateMultiplier for the keyword pool

### Choosing halfLifeDays for temporal decay

| Agent type | Recommended halfLifeDays |
|-----------|--------------------------|
| Daily personal assistant | 30 days |
| Long-range project tracking | 60–90 days |
| Archival / research | Disable or 365+ |
| High-churn operational context | 7–14 days |

### When to enable MMR

Enable MMR when you observe:
- Top-3 results from `memory_search` are near-identical daily note snippets
- Result list feels redundant despite using hybrid scoring
- Users complain "you always show me the same thing"

Tune λ down (toward 0.5) if diversity is insufficient; up (toward 0.9) if results feel scattered.

### QMD search mode selection

| Priority | Use |
|----------|-----|
| Latency < 500ms | `search` (default) |
| Best vector recall | `vsearch` |
| Best overall quality, latency acceptable | `query` (only with a fast CPU/GPU) |

